p.m:
\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{9}{10} + \frac{3}{5}
        \amp = \frac{9}{10} + \frac{6}{10} \\
        \amp = \frac{9 + 6}{10} \\
        \amp = \frac{15}{10} \amp \hbox{We can reduce this by dividing 5 into both the numerator and the denominator.
}\\
        \amp = \frac{3}{2}
\end{aligned}
    }
